Event.info: OSINT - Investigation of Linux.Mirai Trojan family

Attribute.value:
A Trojan for Linux that was named  Linux.Mirai has several predecessors. The first malware program belonging  to  this  family  was  spotted  in  May  2016  and  was  dubbed  Linux.DDoS.87.  At  the  beginning  of August,  a  new  version  of  this  Trojan Linux.DDoS.89 was  discovered.  Finally,  Doctor  Webâ€™s  security researchers investigated the 
Linux.Mirai Trojan found later that month.
